<p>
privacyIDEA SAML adds two factor authentication to the
Univention SAML (SSO) service.
Authentication is done via privacyIDEA. The privacyIDEA service can
be installed on any other member server in your network.
</p>
<p>
Use the following UCR variables to configure privacyIDEA SAML:
<ul>
<li><b>privacyidea/saml/url</b> This is the URL, where your privacyIDEA server is located. Can be  
"https://yourserver/privacyidea".
</li>
<li><b>privacyidea/saml/enable</b> Set this to "True" to activate OTP for SAML.
</li>
<li>
<b>privacyidea/saml/verifypeer</b> Set this to "True" to check the SSL certificate of the 
privacyIDEA server.
</li>
<li>
<b>privacyidea/saml/verifyhost</b> Set this to "True" to check the hostname in the
SSL certificate of the privacyIDEA server.
</li>
</ul>
</p>

